This file gives an overview of options letters used and proposed by Stu,
and a comparison to those used by Make. 


Legend
======

S   Implemented in Stu
M   Specified by POSIX Make
G   Implemented in GNU Make
.   Proposed for Stu 
-   Not proposed for Stu, but the option is purposefully kept unused in
    case we want to use it for Stu 
~   Not applicable to Stu 
x   Incompatible 


List of options
===============

-0  S      Pass a \0-separated dynamic dependency 
-a  S      Consider trivial dependencies to be non-trivial
-b  .   x  Enable backups (GNU Make: compatibility)
-B  .   G  Re-make all
-c  S   x  Explicit target without syntax (GNU Make:  change directory)
-C  S   x  Specify syntax (same as non-option arguments)
-d      G  Print debugging information 
-e  ~ M G  Environment overrides Make macros
-E  S      Explain errors
-f  S M G  File
-F  S      Pass rule on the command line
-g  S      Consider optional dependencies to be non-optional 
-h  S   G  Show help and exit 
-i  . M G  Ignore all errors in commands
-I  .   G  Include path
-j  S   G  Parallel
-J  S      Don't parse Stu syntax in arguments
-k  S M G  Keep going
-K  S      Keep partially built files
-l      G  Number of jobs depends on load average
-L      G  Special handling of symlinks
-m  S   x  Mode; e.g., random order, etc. (GNU Make: compatibility)
-M  S      Seed mode
-n  S x x  Pass a file containing newline-separated file targets, without syntax parsing 
-n  x M G  Dry run (just print commands)
-N  .      Dry run, but build dynamic dependencies 
-o  S   x  Optional dependency
-o  x   G  Mark file as old
-p  S x x  Persistent dependency
-p  x M G  Print database (rule set)
-P  S      Print database (rule set)
-q  S M G  Question mode / Query mode
-Q  S      Quiet mode (suppress stdout messages, except building messages)
-r    M G  No builtin rules
-R      G  No builtin variables
-s  S M G  Silent
-S  - M G  No keep going
-t  . x x  Trivial dependency
-t  x M G  Touch instead of building
-u  .      Consider all files up-to-date 
-v  S   x  Verbose (GNU Make:  show version)
-V  S      Show version and exit
-w  S	x  Short mode (GNU Make:  print directory) 
-W  .   G  What-if mode / assume new (if FILE just had been modified) 
-x  S      Enable /bin/sh -x instead of normal output
-y  S      Disable color output
-Y  S      Enable color output
-z  S      Output statistics

The following options could conceivably be set externally:

-E -Q -s -w -x -y -z
